Update version from 1.7.9 to 1.8.2

Signal following (v1.8.0)
Replaced the dynamic chart_signal_score (which varied across base chart timeframes) with a match to the precomputed s1_score/s2_score/s3_score. This keeps signals consistent regardless of the chart's period.

Input guidance (v1.8.1) 
TF1 is now restricted to ["1","5","15"] to guarantee reliable CLO detection.
Group titles added: Timeframes (TF1 small → TF5 large) and Scoring — TF Weights (adjust only if you understand scoring impact).
Each timeframe input includes a tooltip recommending ascending order.

Dynamic score range (v1.8.2) 
The footer now shows the actual theoretical maximum score: ±(2 * sum of weights) instead of the hardcoded ±15.

Bug fix (v1.8.2) 
Corrected the compilation error on chart_score = na by removing the separate initialisation and assigning the ternary result directly.
